<span style='float: right; width: 280px; height: 187px; margin: 0 0 5px 5px; border: 1px solid black;'><script type='text/javascript'>flash_object ('http://graphics.millsberry.com/buddy/buddy_featured.swf', '280', '187', 'userName=rustin50&buddyTimeStamp=20070322&buddyScriptURL=http%3A%2F%2Fmillsberry.com%2Fbuddy%2Fload_buddy_xml.phtml&unixTimeStamp=1174905749&serverTimeOffset=28800', '', 'exactfit', 'transparent');</script></span>
Meet <b>Rustin</b>, our Citizen of the Week!<br><br>He resides at <a href='/home/?user=rustin50'>25583-A Bluebird Street</a> in Lakeview, the perfect neighborhood for a natural athlete. He jogs alongside the lake when the weather is nice, and has made many friends in the area since moving in on July 30, 2006.<br><br>When you first meet him, he may seem a little shy, but he soon opens up and is very friendly. He is laidback and thoughtful but gets especially riled up when the topic of baseball comes up. He's a <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/gamepages/flashgame_ctp.phtml?game_id=160">Sherman Home Run Derby</a> champion who is constantly working on improving his swing for maximum power, so he has plenty to say about the subject!<br><br>His home is carefully decorated in a minimalist style that keeps things simple and uncluttered. He also has his trophies and Chip the Wolf collection prominently displayed. His favorite colors include dark blue and silver, and he has designed his home in equally subtle shades that reflect his calm and collected personality.<br><br>So stop by Rustin's place and get to know him. Compare dojo stats or discuss books (one of his favorite hobbies is reading). He's a solid guy everyone should know. <br><br>Thanks for being a good citizen, Rustin, and congrats on being named Citizen of the Week!</div>
